.SH INTERFACE
.IX Header "INTERFACE"
.SS "Class (static) methods"
.IX Subsection "Class (static) methods"
These methods are used to find an opcode.
.PP
\fIget_opcode_by_name\fR
.IX Subsection "get_opcode_by_name"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        my $object = Bitcoin::Crypto::Script::Opcode\->get_opcode_by_name($name);
.Ve
.PP
Finds an opcode by its name (\f(CW\*(C`OP_XXX\*(C'\fR) and returns an object instance.
.PP
If opcode was not found an exception is raised
(\f(CW\*(C`Bitcoin::Crypto::Exception::ScriptOpcode\*(C'\fR).
.PP
\fIget_opcode_by_code\fR
.IX Subsection "get_opcode_by_code"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        my $object = Bitcoin::Crypto::Script::Opcode\->get_opcode_by_code($int);
.Ve
.PP
Finds an opcode by its code (integer in range 0\-255) and returns an object
instance.
.PP
If opcode was not found, an \f(CW\*(C`UNKNOWN\*(C'\fR opcode is returned which marks the
script as invalid on execution.
